## 🎯 What is a Credential Harvesting Site?

It’s a fake login page that mimics a legitimate service (e.g., Google, Facebook, PayPal) to trick users into entering their credentials. The site then captures the username/password via form submission.

---

## ✅ Example Code: Simple HTML + JavaScript + PHP

### 📄 `index.html` — The Fake Login Form
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><title>Login - SecureBank</title></head>
<body style="background:#f0f0f0; text-align:center;">
    <h1>SecureBank Online Banking</h1>

    <form action="login.php" method="POST">
        <input type="text" name="username" placeholder="Username" required><br><br>
        <input type="password" name="password" placeholder="Password" required><br><br>
        <button type="submit">Login</button>
    </form>

    <p style="margin-top:20px; color:#666;">© 2025 SecureBank. All rights reserved.</p>
</body>
